> Imagine if you don't have any issues, you just receive information
  that you don't have access to this file, how you will give access to this:

  - so basically, if i don't have access to a file, first i would check the current
    permissions of the file

  - for example, i would use ls -l <file_name> to see the read, write, and execute
    permissions

  - based on that, if i have permission to modify it, i can use chmod to add the required
    access, like read or execute permission

  - if the issue is related to ownership, i can check the owner and group, and if
    required update it using chown

  - if i don't have sufficient privileges, i would use sudo or request access from
    the administrator


    ls -ls file - check permissions
    chmod +x file - give execute
    chmod 755 file - full control
    chown user file - change owner
